'''Reichelsheim Airport''' is a [[general aviation]] [[airport]] located in German state of [[Hesse]], just 30 minutes north of [[Frankfurt am Main]].

==Facilities==
The airport resides at an [[elevation]] of {{convert|398|ft|0}} above [[mean sea level]]. It has a [[asphalt]] paved [[runway]] designated 18/36 which measures {{convert|1300|x|23|m|0}}.
It offers [[runway]] - and [[taxiway]] illumination, [[Precision Approach Path Indicator|PAPI]], [[REIL]] and [[Approach Lighting System|ALS]].
Aircraft up to 8,000&nbsp;kg (17,636&nbsp;lb) are allowed to land at the airport.

The aerodrome also serves as an important [[heliport]] for medevac and [[Very Important Person|VIP]] transports. [[Johanniter-Unfall-Hilfe]] e. V. is present with its 24h/365days medevac helicopters Christoph Hessen and Christoph Rhein-Main.

==Airlines and destinations==
There are no scheduled services to and from Reichelsheim Airport.

